      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 232: `scheduleBackoffRetry()` assumes the caller holds `mutex`, but the implementation does not enforce that and it is also called from `noteConnectionFailure()`. This makes the timer state (`retryTimer_`, `retryArmed_`, `retryAt_`) fragile and easy to race if future callers follow the public-looking function literally. Either make `scheduleBackoffRetry()` take the lock itself, or rename/split it to make the locked precondition explicit and assert it where possible. A safer pattern is to keep all timer state changes inside the helper:\n```suggestion\nvoid\nSwarmManager::scheduleBackoffRetry(std::chrono::steady_clock::time_point when)\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex);\n    if (retryArmed_ \u0026\u0026 retryAt_ \u003c\u003d when)\n        return;\n    ...\n}\n```",
